<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Bush" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Bush,</orth> thick shrub: <cit><quote>the thorny brambles and embracing --es,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 629" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 629</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ven 629" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 629</bibl> <bibl n="shak. luc 973" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 973</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 18</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.7" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 1, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.137" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 137</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.1.61" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.1.61" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 61</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.406" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 406</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.406" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 406</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.22.406" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.22.406" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 22</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.114" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 3, 114</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.423" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 423</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 2.4.305" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 4, 305</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.292" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 292</bibl>. <cit><quote>the thief doth fear each b. an officer,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.6.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 6, 12</bibl></cit>; cf. <bibl n="shak. luc 973" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 973</bibl> and <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 22</bibl>. <cit><quote>be married under a b. like a beggar,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.3.85" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 3, 85</bibl></cit>. <emph>good wine needs no b.</emph> As Epil. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.3.85" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 3, 85</bibl> 6 (alluding to the bush of ivy which was usually hung out at vintners' doors). <cit><quote>birds never limed no secret --es fear,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 88" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 88</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>am I your bird? I mean to shift my b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 5.2.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. V, 2, 46</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>myself have limed a b. for her,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.3.91" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 3, 91</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>limed --es to betray thy wings,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.4.54" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 54</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>limed in a b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.6.13" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 6, 13</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I have a fine hawk for the b.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.3.248" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 3, 248</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>